[[ja:%E4%B9%BE%E9%9A%86]]
[[sn:Qianlong]]
[[ja:乾隆]]

'''Kenryū''' (乾隆, {{ill|Manchu language|ja|満洲語|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: {{mongol|ᠠᠪᡴᠠᡳ<br>ᠸᡝᡥᡳᠶᡝᡥᡝ|lt=abkai wehiyehe}}) is an era name used during the reign of the {{ill|Qianlong Emperor|ja|乾隆帝|lt=Kyanryū Emperor|lt_ja=高宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Qing|ja|清|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. It spans from {{ill|1736|ja|1736年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|1795|ja|1795th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}.

Because of the "One reign, one era system" ({{ill|One reign, one era system|ja|一世一元の制|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}), the emperor is referred to as '''{{ill|Qianlong Emperor|ja|乾隆帝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}'''.

In Chinese history, this era name was used for 60 years, making it the second-longest used after {{ill|Kangxi|ja|康熙|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}.

